>git --version :- returns version if git present
commit :- to save the changes in the file to git
stage :- to make the files ready to be committed
>git status:- returns if all the files are tracked,committed and modifications
>git add --all & *git add -A :- stages all the files in git 
>git add . :-stages only the files in the current directory 
>git reset :-reverses the staging process u did
>git add * :- stages every change in git except any deletions
>git add filename.extension :- we can stage individual files
>git add *.extension :- we can stage all files in the current directory with that extension
>git rm filename.extension :- to delete and stage the deletion
>git rm -f filename.extension :- to force delete if the files is not committed but staged
>git rm --cached filename.extension :- removes the file from gits tracking but not from ur computer
>git rm -r foldername :- to delete an entire folder
>git commit -m "comment" :- to commit the git with a cmnt
>git config --global user.email "youremail":- to save every git file on this system to this email
>git config --global user.name "yourname" :- to save your name for every git commits
>git config --local     "           "      :- using this u can only set for the current repositoty not for ur entire system
>git branch :- lists all branches and puts a "*" on current branch
>git branch newbranchname :- creates a new branch and will be the clone of your current branch
>git checkout branchname :- teleports to the specified branch
>git switch branchname :-      "      "   "      "       "
